.TH "mlx90632_perform_measurement" 9 "mlx90632_perform_measurement" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mlx90632_perform_measurement \- Trigger and retrieve current measurement cycle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mlx90632_perform_measurement
.BI "(struct mlx90632_data *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
pointer to mlx90632_data object containing regmap information
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Perform a measurement and return latest measurement cycle position reported
by sensor. This is a blocking function for 500ms, as that is default sensor
refresh rate.
